            <p>ALBANUS L. SMITH &#38; CO.&#44;<lb/>
                3045 CHESTNUT ST.<lb/>
                ORNAMENTAL IRON WORK&#44;<lb/>
                BUILDERS&#39; IRON&#44; STAIRS&#44; RAILINGS&#44; DOORS&#44; SHUTTERS&#44;<lb/>
                GUARDS&#44; GRILLES&#44; WIRE WORK.<lb/></p>
            <p>PHILADELPHIA&#44; April 18&#44; 1890<lb/>
                Rev. Dr S. <sic>Morias</sic><lb/></p>
            <p>546 N. 5&#44; St<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Dear Sir&#44;&#45;&#45;At a meeting of the Siberian Exile Petition<lb/> Association&#44; and the Siberian Exile Relief Committee&#44; the meeting<lb/> adjourned&#44; until 3.30&#44; P. M. Saturday afternoon&#44; having appointed<lb/> a committee to prepare a plan&#44; and arrange the details for a Fusion<lb/> of the two bodies&#44; so that their work may be successful in obtain&#45;<lb/>ing the united voice of the AMERICAN PEOPLE&#44; on behalf of the un&#45;<lb/>fortunate Political Exiles in Siberia.<lb/></p>
            <p>You are therefore invited to attend the meeting to&#45;morrow after&#45;<lb/>noon&#44; Saturday April 19th&#44; at 1307 Arch St. Second Floor Front&#44;<lb/> &#40;Friends Institute Room&#41; when a full attendance is desired to act<lb/> on the report of the Committee.<lb/>  Yours truly&#44;<lb/> A. L. SMITH&#44;<lb/> Secretary Pro&#45;Tem.<lb/> Per. A. P. C.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
